(141, 'Takayuki Negishi', 'b7ab2fc0-6124-4cde-a7c8-1caa65ae5d0d', 'Negishi Takayuki;ś†ĻŚ≤ł Ť≤īŚĻł;ś†ĻŚ≤łŤ≤īŚĻł;ś†ĻŚ≤łŤīĶŚĻł', 'Tokyo[8dc97297-ac95-4d33-82bc-e07fab26fb5f]', '100073[2db42837-c832-3c27-b4a3-08198f75693c]', '1995-08-06', NULL, NULL, '200006', '2000031;2001334', '1', '[Discogs (6)‚Ė†https://www.discogs.com/artist/583713];[MusicBrainz (6)‚Ė†https://musicbrainz.org/artist/b7ab2fc0-6124-4cde-a7c8-1caa65ae5d0d];[IMDb (6)‚Ė†https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0624381/];;[FilmAffinity (6)‚Ė†https://www.filmaffinity.com/us/name.php?name-id=214572282][Mubi (6)‚Ė†https://mubi.com/en/cast/takayuki-negishi];[Last.fm (6)‚Ė†https://www.last.fm/music/Takayuki+Negishi];[VGMDb (6)‚Ė†https://vgmdb.net/artist/808];[Apple Music (4)‚Ė†https://music.apple.com/co/artist/takayuki-negishi/321124847];[Deezer (3)‚Ė†https://www.deezer.com/artist/12629641];[Spotify (3)‚Ė†https://open.spotify.com/artist/1zsqWi4p1YjevjaEWlHwZv];[YouTube (3)‚Ė†https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCaCRPrjNXvBPzJ3QRYz7P0A];[AnimeSongs (7)‚Ė†https://www.animesonglyrics.com/artist/takayuki-negishi];[Genius (7)‚Ė†https://genius.com/artists/Negishi-takayuki];[RuTracker (5)‚Ė†https://rutracker.org/forum/tracker.php?nm=Takayuki%20Negishi];[The Pirate Bay (5)‚Ė†https://thepiratebay.org/search.php?q=Takayuki+Negishi&audio=on];[YouTube Music (3)‚Ė†https://music.youtube.com/channel/UCaCRPrjNXvBPzJ3QRYz7P0A];[wikidata (6)‚Ė†https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q2329597]', 'Takayuki Negishi (Japanese: ś†ĻŚ≤ł Ť≤īŚĻł, Hepburn: Negishi Takayuki, born August 6, 1961) is a Japanese composer, music arranger, and synthesizer operator. He is best known for his extensive work in the anime industry, particularly for composing the scores of the Cardcaptor Sakura franchise and the Tokyo Mew Mew series. Negishi is a prominent member of the music production company Imagine, where he frequently collaborates with other renowned composers such as Kohei Tanaka and Kow Otani.\nNegishi began his career in 1983 as a synthesizer operator and programmer. His early work involved providing technical support and arrangements for pop artists and soundtracks, including the City Hunter and Mobile Police Patlabor series. In the late 1990s, he rose to prominence as a lead composer. His work on Cardcaptor Sakura (1998) is widely celebrated for its \"magical\" orchestral sound, which blended classical strings with upbeat pop rhythms and jazz-influenced chord progressions. He returned to the franchise nearly two decades later to compose the score for the Clear Card arc in 2018. Beyond television anime, Negishi has also composed for video games, most notably the early entries of the fighting game series Bloody Roar.', 'http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/T/Takayuki Negishi/Audio/Albums/1998.12.19. Cardcaptor Sakura Original Soundtrack 2/20. Nukumori no Kioku (Memories of Warmth).mp3', 'Mew Zakuro no Theme‚Ė†Heavenly‚Ė†Bringer of the New Age‚Ė†Want Some More‚Ė†Nap Time‚Ė†It%36s My Turn Now‚Ė†This One%36s for You‚Ė†Nukumori no Kioku‚Ė†Lust in Peace‚Ė†Scourge of the Night‚Ė†No Joke‚Ė†Ready‚Ė†No One Can Stop Me‚Ė†THEME FROM LUPIN ‚ÖĘ%3696 - TV version‚Ė†Sawayakana Asa‚Ė†You%36re Dead‚Ė†Akogare‚Ė†Clow Card‚Ė†THEME FROM LUPIN III%3696 (TV version)‚Ė†Yume‚Ė†Panic‚Ė†Yasuragi no Hi‚Ė†Genki Ippai‚Ė†Shiawase no Sakura Namiki‚Ė†Setsunai Kimochi‚Ė†Kibou no Yokan‚Ė†Chikashitsu‚Ė†Roller Blade‚Ė†Tanjou! Card Captor‚Ė†Hoe?‚Ė†Sakura no THEME II‚Ė†Tanoshii Hitotoki‚Ė†Shopping‚Ė†Victory‚Ė†Sakura no THEME I‚Ė†THEME FROM LUPIN ‚ÖĘ %3696‚Ė†Defenders of Legacy (Opening)‚Ė†Kero-chan no THEME‚Ė†Clow Card o Nigasu Na!‚Ė†Heartbreak‚Ė†On The Special Day‚Ė†Into the Battlefield‚Ė†Mew Lettuce no Theme‚Ė†Okasan no Omokage‚Ė†Taiketsu!!‚Ė†Hangeki Kaishi‚Ė†Shaoran no THEME‚Ė†Koi-gokoro‚Ė†Mew Ichigo no Theme‚Ė†Mou Hitori no Eriol‚Ė†Mew Mint no Theme‚Ė†MOJI-MOJI‚Ė†Kusen‚Ė†Hoshi no Chikara‚Ė†Ganbare Sakura‚Ė†Kyouteki Shutsugen‚Ė†Ashidori Karuku‚Ė†Omoide ga Kiechau‚Ė†Sorezore no Omoi‚Ė†Saigo no Shinpan‚Ė†Tomadoi‚Ė†Clow Reed no Theme‚Ė†Bad Moon Rising (Yugo)‚Ė†Fuuin-kaijo‚Ė†