(142, 'Naomi Kaitani', '078669bb-9a2a-4665-966f-7325923a4e5a', 'KAIYA Naomi;Naomi', 'Tokushima[da3ba6e6-6602-43f1-868a-412a0269dd87]', '100073[2db42837-c832-3c27-b4a3-08198f75693c]', '1998-08-11', NULL, '152;151;150;149;148;147;146;145;144;143;153', '200012;200006', '2001305;2000031;2000707', '1', '[Official Website (2)‚Ė†https://kaitaninaomi.com/];[Facebook (2)‚Ė†https://www.facebook.com/naomi.kaitani.1/];[MusicBrainz (6)‚Ė†https://musicbrainz.org/artist/078669bb-9a2a-4665-966f-7325923a4e5a];[Discogs (6)‚Ė†https://www.discogs.com/artist/4278598-Naomi-Kaitani];[VGMDb (6)‚Ė†https://vgmdb.net/artist/10262];[Last.fm (6)‚Ė†https://www.last.fm/es/music/Kaitani+Naomi];[Apple Music (4)‚Ė†https://music.apple.com/co/artist/%E7%9A%86%E8%B0%B7%E5%B0%9A%E7%BE%8E/446769758];[Deezer (3)‚Ė†https://www.deezer.com/artist/185750497];[Tidal (3)‚Ė†https://stage.tidal.com/artist/34842268];[Spotify (3)‚Ė†https://open.spotify.com/artist/6a9dX5C57biSqChhn5Bg1F];[YouTube (3)‚Ė†https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCp1pRMciDfYSnQcEu2eceVg];[YouTube Music (3)‚Ė†https://music.youtube.com/channel/UCp1pRMciDfYSnQcEu2eceVg];[Soundcloud (3)‚Ė†https://soundcloud.com/naomi_kaitani];[YouTube (3)‚Ė†https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCp1pRMciDfYSnQcEu2eceVg];[Wikidata (6)‚Ė†https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q11580985];[RuTracker (5)‚Ė†https://rutracker.org/forum/tracker.php?nm=Naomi%20Kaitani];[The Pirate Bay (5)‚Ė†https://thepiratebay.org/search.php?q=Naomi+Kaitani&audio=on]', 'Naomi Kaitani (Japanese: ÁöÜŤį∑ ŚįöÁĺé, Hepburn: Kaitani Naomi, born August 11, 1978) is a Japanese singer-songwriter, pianist, and composer. She is best recognized internationally for performing and composing \"Tooi Kono Machi de\" (\"In This Distant Town\"), the theme song for the 1999 animated feature film Cardcaptor Sakura: The Movie.\nBorn in Tokushima Prefecture, Kaitani is known for her soulful, clear vocal style and her ability to blend pop, folk, and classical elements in her piano-driven compositions.\nKaitani made her major-label debut under Victor Entertainment in 1999. Her breakout single, \"Tooi Kono Machi de\", was released on August 11, 1999, to coincide with the first Cardcaptor Sakura film. Unlike many anime theme song performers who are primarily vocalists, Kaitani wrote both the lyrics and music for the track, which became a fan favorite for its nostalgic and hopeful tone.\nFollowing her work with the Cardcaptor Sakura franchise, she continued to release independent albums and perform live, often focusing on themes of \"hometown\" (furusato) and the natural beauty of her native Tokushima. In 2016, she contributed lyrics and vocals (under the moniker naomi) to the soundtrack of the anime series God Eater.\nKaitani\'s music is often described as \"healing\" or \"pastoral.\" Her performances typically feature her playing the piano while singing, with arrangements that emphasize acoustic instruments. Her later work has moved toward a \"self-produced\" aesthetic, where she handles arrangement and engineering on many of her indie releases.', 'http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/N/Naomi Kaitani/Audio/Singles/1998.08.11. Tooi Kono Machi De/01. Tooi Kono Machi De.mp3^http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/N/Naomi Kaitani/Audio/Singles/1998.08.11. Tooi Kono Machi De/02. Sepia no Hi.mp3', 'ťĀ†„ĀĄ„Āď„ĀģŤ°ó„Āß‚Ė†Tooi Kono Machi De‚Ė†„āĽ„ÉĒ„āĘ„Āģśó•‚Ė†Sepia no Hi‚Ė†Tooi kono machi de (karaoke)‚Ė†Toi no Machide‚Ė†Sepia no hi (original karaoke)‚Ė†ťĀ†„ĀĄ„Āď„ĀģŤ°ó„Āß - self cover ver.‚Ė†tooi kono machi de (original karaoke)‚Ė†śĶ∑„Āł‚Ė†Tooi kono Machide‚Ė†„āľ„ÉĒ„āĘ„Āģśó•‚Ė†śįīŚĻ≥Á∑ö„ĀģŚĹľśĖĻ„ĀęŤ¶č„Āą„āč„āā„Āģ‚Ė†ŤŅú„ĀĄ„Āď„ĀģŤ°ó„Āß‚Ė†„Ā§„Āć„Āā„Āč„āä‚Ė†Blue Sky‚Ė†In this Distant Town‚Ė†Rebirth‚Ė†Ś§Ź„ĀģÁĶā„āŹ„āä„ĀģťÄö„āäťõ®‚Ė†Lovely‚Ė†It%36s My Life‚Ė†Memories of Wind‚Ė†Working Girl‚Ė†„Āä„āĄ„Āô„ĀŅ„Āģ„ĀÜ„Āü‚Ė†„ā§„É≥„Éá„ā£„āī‚Ė†Sepia no Hibi‚Ė†River‚Ė†A Little Hymn‚Ė†šļ§Ś∑ģÁāĻ‚Ė†tooi kono machi de (original k‚Ė†ÁôĺŚĻīśĄõś≠Ć‚Ė†ťĀ†„ĀĄ„Āď„ĀģŤ°ó„Ā¶„āô‚Ė†śúÄśěú„Ā¶‚Ė†„Ā°„ĀĄ„Āē„Ā™„Āĺ„ĀĽ„ĀÜ‚Ė†ťĀ†„ĀĄ„Āď„ĀģŤ°ó„Āß („ā™„É™„āł„Éä„Éę„