(144, 'Aya Hisakawa', 'c3c7b8a6-8e38-4114-b49e-3f8cc427f12a', 'šĻÖŚ∑Ě Á∂ĺ;šĻÖŚ∑ĚÁ∂ĺ', 'Kaizuka[a513ebe0-3022-4e27-938c-20c81a917f0c]', '100073[2db42837-c832-3c27-b4a3-08198f75693c]', '1968-11-12', NULL, '152;151;150;149;148;147;146;145;153;143;142', '200012', '2000707', '1', '[Official Website (2)‚Ė†http://www.aoni.co.jp/actress/ha/hisakawa-aya.html];[Discogs (6)‚Ė†https://www.discogs.com/artist/271059];[Spotify (3)‚Ė†https://open.spotify.com/artist/1RMtLtxNv4i0IunDlZnozf];[IMDb (6)‚Ė†https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0386752/];[Anime News Network (6)‚Ė†https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/encyclopedia/people.php?id=503];[VGMdb (6)‚Ė†https://vgmdb.net/artist/3212];[VIAF (6)‚Ė†http://viaf.org/viaf/258736141];[Wikidata (6)‚Ė†https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q49573];[Rutracker (5)‚Ė†https://rutracker.org/forum/tracker.php?nm=Aya%20Hisakawa];[The Pirate Bay (5)‚Ė†https://thepiratebay.org/search.php?q=Aya+Hisakawa&audio=on];[Wikipedia (6)‚Ė†https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aya_Hisakawa];[Genius (7)‚Ė†https://genius.com/artists/Aya-Hisakawa];[MusicBrainz (6)‚Ė†https://musicbrainz.org/artist/c3c7b8a6-8e38-4114-b49e-3f8cc427f12a]', 'Aya Hisakawa (šĻÖŚ∑Ě Á∂ĺ, Hisakawa Aya, born November 12, 1968) is a prolific Japanese voice actress and singer from Kaizuka, Osaka. Affiliated with Aoni Production, she has been a mainstay in the anime and video game industries since her debut in 1988. Hisakawa is widely recognized for voicing several iconic characters in 1990s anime, most notably Ami Mizuno (Sailor Mercury) in Sailor Moon, Skuld in Oh My Goddess!, and Keroberos in Cardcaptor Sakura. In 2018, she was selected to succeed the late Hiromi Tsuru as the voice of Bulma in the Dragon Ball franchise.\nOriginally known for playing \"innocent\" or \"genki\" girls, Hisakawa‚Äôs range has expanded as her voice matured. She is now frequently cast in \"cool beauty,\" mature, or authoritative roles, such as Retsu Unohana in Bleach and Palutena in the Kid Icarus and Super Smash Bros. series. A native of Osaka, she occasionally performs roles using her natural Kansai dialect, which adds a distinct regional flavor to her characters. Beyond voice acting, she is an accomplished J-pop singer, having released multiple solo albums and singles throughout the 1990s. She was also a member of the voice actress singing group Goddess Family Club.', NULL, 'ÁßėŚĮÜ‚Ė†ŚźĆ„Āėś∂ô„āíŚąÜ„ĀĎŚźą„Ā£„Ā¶‚Ė†śúą„Ā®Ś§™ťôĹ„Āģ„āĀ„Āź„āä‚Ė†Jingle Bells‚Ė†„ĀĄ„Ā£„Āó„āá„Āę„ĀÜ„Āü„Āä‚Ė†Moonlight Densetsu (The Finals)‚Ė†Touch my heart‚Ė†„āł„É≥„āį„Éę„Éô„Éę‚Ė†ś°úśó•ŚíĆ‚Ė†Sunday‚Ė†„Āā„Āó„Āü„āā„Āĺ„ĀüŤá™ŤĽĘŤĽä‚Ė†Hallelujah‚Ė†Hi-Ka-Ri‚Ė†Voice In The Paradise‚Ė†Ś§™ťôĹ„āíśćú„Āó„Ā¶‚Ė†ťĚí„ĀĄÁ©ļ„āíśäĪ„Āć„Āó„āĀ„Āü„ĀĄ‚Ė†Rainy Blue‚Ė†Shiny Day‚Ė†ťĀ•„Āč„Ā™ťĘ®‚Ė†Someday„ÉĽ„ÉĽ„ÉĽSomebody„ÉĽ„ÉĽ„ÉĽ‚Ė†ťáĎśú®ÁäÄ‚Ė†śļÄśúą„Āģ„Āó„āŹ„ĀĖ‚Ė†Cookie%36s Story‚Ė†Tsuki to taiyou no meguri‚Ė†Issho ni Utao‚Ė†Take It Easy‚Ė†DREAM OF YOU‚Ė†śįī„Āģ„É©„Éď„É™„É≥„āĻ‚Ė†Someday... Somebody...‚Ė†ŤĶ§„ĀĄÁ†āśôāŤ®ą‚Ė†ŚÉē„ĀģŚ•Ĺ„Āć„Ā™„Ā≤„Ā®‚Ė†„ÉĒ„Éľ„āĻ„āĪ„Āģ„ĀÜ„Āü‚Ė†Small Hand‚Ė†„Ā†„ĀĄ„Āė„āá„Éľ„Ā∂„Ā£„Ā£!!‚Ė†Don%36t Worry and Believe My Love‚Ė†Crystal Generation‚Ė†śúą„ĀģŚ§ú„Āę‚Ė†šļļÁĒü„ÄĀÁ•≠„āä„āĄ„Ā£„Ā£‚Ė†So Bad Boy‚Ė†śĀč„ĀĮťĘ®„Āĺ„Āč„Āõ‚Ė†Himitsu‚Ė†„Āä„āā„ĀĄ„Āß„Āģ„Ā™„Āč‚Ė†„É†„Éľ„É≥„É©„ā§„ÉąšľĚŤ™¨‚Ė†śĀčšļļ„Āę„ĀĮ„Ā™„āĆ„Ā™„ĀĄ„ĀĎ„Ā©‚Ė†Girl%36s Holiday‚Ė†Ť¶č„Āą„Ā™„ĀĄÁŅľ‚Ė†Ashita mo Mata Jitensha‚Ė†Onaji Namida wo Wakeatte‚Ė†Wait For Me!‚Ė†Ś§ČŤ≤Ć‚Ė†„Āā„Ā™„Āü„ĀģÁě≥„Āę„ĀÜ„Ā§„āčśôāťĖď‚Ė†ťĀé„ĀéŚéĽ„āä„Āóśā≤„Āó„ĀŅ„Āü„Ā°„Āł‚Ė†for you for me‚Ė†„ÉÄ„ā§„Éä„Éě„ā§„ÉąCAT‚Ė†ŚŅÉ„Āĺ„ĀßśäĪ„Āć„Āó„āĀ„āČ„āĆ„Āü„āČ‚Ė†Someday‚Ä¶Somebody‚Ä¶‚Ė†„āĶ„āĮ„É©‚Ė†ŤĶ§„ĀĄ„āĻ„ÉĚ„Éľ„ÉĄ„āę„Éľ‚Ė†Someday...Somebody...‚Ė†śćē„Āĺ„āČ„Ā™„ĀĄ„āą‚Ė†Let Me Try Again‚Ė†Koi no Housoku‚Ė†Moonlight Densetsu‚Ė†Let Me Try Again [From Sparkling Crystal Legend Astal]‚Ė†śĀč„Āģ„āĮ„Éľ„Éá„āŅ„Éľ„ÉĽ„āī„Éľ„āī„Éľ‚Ė†„Éę„Éľ„āł„É•„āí„Ā≤„Āď„ĀÜ„āą‚Ė†„āĻ„Éö„ā∑„É£„Éę„É°„Éč„É•„Éľ„āí„Āā„Ā™„Āü„Āę‚Ė†Stay by me‚Ė†Ś§Ę„Āģšł≠„ĀĮśĀčšļļ‚Ė†Merry Christmas‚Ė†śĀč„Āģś≥ēŚČá‚Ė†[DHY IS] Full Moon Light {Mangetsu no Shiwaza}‚Ė†Will you stay‚Ė†śôāťĖď„āí