(145, 'CHAKA', '900e9144-019d-4043-86cb-ec0e127c39d0', 'Mami Yasunori;ŚģČŚČáÁúěŚģü', 'Osaka[30bcaa92-9870-4798-be1a-4e0036755316]', '100073[2db42837-c832-3c27-b4a3-08198f75693c]', '1960-07-16', NULL, '152;151;150;149;148;147;146;153;144;143;142', '200012', '2000707', '1', '[Official Website (2)‚Ė†http://www.ask.ne.jp/~komiya/mus/ChakaHP.htm];[VGMdb (6)‚Ė†https://vgmdb.net/artist/19358];[Wikidata (6)‚Ė†https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q11193215];[Rutracker (5)‚Ė†https://rutracker.org/forum/tracker.php?nm=CHAKA];[The Pirate Bay (5)‚Ė†https://thepiratebay.org/search.php?q=CHAKA&audio=on];[Wikipedia (6)‚Ė†https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CHAKA];[Genius (7)‚Ė†https://genius.com/artists/CHAKA];[MusicBrainz (6)‚Ė†https://musicbrainz.org/artist/900e9144-019d-4043-86cb-ec0e127c39d0]', 'Chaka (born March 16, 1960), also known by her birth name Yasunori Mami (ŚģČŚČá ÁúěŚģü), is a prominent Japanese jazz and pop singer, lyricist, and educator. She is most widely recognized internationally for her tenure as the lead vocalist of the sophisticated pop duo PSY¬∑S (pronounced \"Siz\"), which she formed with multi-instrumentalist Masaya Matsuura in 1985. Chaka began her professional career in the early 1980s, gaining attention for her powerful, clear vocal range and expressive delivery. Her career is generally categorized into three distinct phases: The PSY¬∑S Era (1985‚Äď1996): As the voice of PSY¬∑S, she became a staple of the Japanese \"New Music\" and synth-pop scenes. The duo achieved significant commercial success with hits like \"Angel Night\" (the opening theme for the anime City Hunter 2) and \"Friends or Lovers.\" Solo Pop Career: Following the disbandment of PSY¬∑S in 1996, she released several solo albums, often collaborating with high-profile producers and exploring more eclectic, experimental pop sounds. Jazz and Education: In the 2000s, Chaka pivoted toward her lifelong passion for jazz. She has since established herself as a respected jazz vocalist, performing regularly in clubs across Japan. She also serves as a vocal coach and educator, sharing her expertise in phrasing and technique with aspiring singers.\n\nChaka is noted for her technical precision and ability to navigate complex, layered arrangements‚ÄĒa necessity during her time with PSY¬∑S, where the music often blended progressive rock structures with electronic pop. While her early work is synonymous with the vibrant aesthetic of 1980s and 90s Japan, her transition to jazz highlighted a more intimate, soulful side of her artistry. In addition to her music, she has contributed lyrics to various projects and provided vocals for several video game soundtracks and commercial jingles, cementing her status as a versatile fixture in the Japanese music industry for over four decades.', 'http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/C/CHAKA/Audio/Singles/2000.07.12. Ashita e no Melody/01. Ashita e no Melody.mp3^http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/C/CHAKA/Audio/Singles/2000.07.12. Ashita e no Melody/02. Blue as the Sky.mp3', 'śėéśó•„Āł„Āģ„É°„É≠„Éá„ā£„Éľ‚Ė†Ashita E No Melody‚Ė†blue as the sky‚Ė†Embuelto‚Ė†Badman Style‚Ė†Africa Symphony‚Ė†Via Tembisa‚Ė†Asu he no Melody‚Ė†Ashita he no Melody‚Ė†La Miro A Los Ojos‚Ė†Gyal Whine‚Ė†Sail Away (Vocal)‚Ė†Baba‚Ė†Heaven [Remix]‚Ė†Toute la Night‚Ė†Dans le Vroum‚Ė†Pa ni love‚Ė†„Āā„Āó„Āü„Ā¶„āď„Āć„Āę„Ā™„āĆ‚Ė†sail away(vocal)‚Ė†Earth extinction‚Ė†Mindless lambs‚Ė†Asueno Melody‚Ė†Despair‚Ė†Democracy and Death‚Ė†Ashitae no Merodii‚Ė†Ashita e no MERODII‚Ė†„Āú„āď„Āĺ„ĀĄ„ĀĖ„āÄ„āČ„ĀĄ„Āģ„ĀÜ„Āü‚Ė†sail away - vocal‚Ė†Genocide‚Ė†Scientific obsession‚Ė†Victims‚Ė†It Takes Two‚Ė†Never Again‚Ė†Ain`t Nobody‚Ė†Airborne‚Ė†„ÉŹ„ÉÉ„āĮ„Éę„Éô„É™„Éľ„Éē„É¨„É≥„āļ‚Ė†Call meÔĹěŤ¶ö„Āą„Ā¶„ĀĄ„Ā¶„ĀĽ„Āó„ĀĄ‚Ė†moonstruck‚Ė†Ashitahe no melody‚Ė†ashita he no MERODEII‚Ė†Tell Me Why‚Ė†Echale Agua‚Ė†ŚÉēÁ≠Č„ĀĮ„āā„Ā£„Ā®„Āô„ĀĒ„ĀĄ„ĀĮ„Āö‚Ė†Spring Is Here‚Ė†Now We‚Ė†Ť™ėśÉĎ„Āģ„ÉŹ„É≥„Éě„Éľ‚Ė†Dawn - „ĀĮ„Āė„Āĺ„āä„ĀģŚĒĄ‚Ė†Loving Feet - śĀč„Āô„āčŚŹ≥Ť∂≥„ÄĀŚ∑¶Ť∂≥‚Ė†Lemon„ĀģŚčáśįó‚Ė†Ashita e no MERODI‚Ė†„ÉŹ„ÉÉ„ÉĒ„Éľ„ā¶„āß„Éá„ā£„É