(146, 'chihiRo', '6df189ad-8278-4b98-ae78-ed5e7ca428d6', 'Chihiro Kiryu;ś°źÁĒüŚćÉŚľė', 'Tokyo[8dc97297-ac95-4d33-82bc-e07fab26fb5f]', '100073[2db42837-c832-3c27-b4a3-08198f75693c]', NULL, NULL, '152;151;150;149;148;147;153;145;144;143;142', '200012', '2000707', '1', '[Discogs (6)‚Ė†https://www.discogs.com/artist/7732023];[Official Website (2)‚Ė†https://sound.jp/chihiroencyclopedia/];[VGMdb (6)‚Ė†https://vgmdb.net/artist/40167];[Rutracker (5)‚Ė†https://rutracker.org/forum/tracker.php?nm=chihiRo];[The Pirate Bay (5)‚Ė†https://thepiratebay.org/search.php?q=chihiRo&audio=on];[Wikipedia (6)‚Ė†https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/chihiRo];[Genius (7)‚Ė†https://genius.com/artists/chihiRo];[MusicBrainz (6)‚Ė†https://musicbrainz.org/artist/6df189ad-8278-4b98-ae78-ed5e7ca428d6]', 'Chihiro Kiryu (ś°źÁĒü ŚćÉŚľė, KiryŇę Chihiro), better known by the mononym chihiro, is a Japanese singer-songwriter, composer, and arranger. She is most widely recognized for her contribution to the 1998 anime series Cardcaptor Sakura, for which she wrote, composed, and performed the song \"Honey\", used as the second ending theme (episodes 36‚Äď46). Kiryu\'s work is characterized by its soft, melodic J-pop qualities, often blending acoustic elements with gentle electronic arrangements. Her most famous work, \"Honey,\" became a fan favorite for its sentimental lyrics and \"healing\" vocal style, which contrasted with the high-energy opening themes of the series. The single, released on May 21, 1999, through Victor Entertainment, also included a version of the song performed by Sakura Tange (the voice actress for the protagonist, Sakura Kinomoto). Beyond her solo performance as \"chihiro,\" she has extensive credits in the Japanese music industry as a composer and arranger for various anime soundtracks and media projects, often credited under her full name, Chihiro Kiryu.', 'http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/C/chihiRo/Audio/Singles/1999.05.21. Honey/01. Honey.mp3', 'Honey‚Ė†„Āö„āč„ĀĄ„āą‚Ä¶‚Ė†Last Kiss‚Ė†RESET‚Ė†