(147, 'Hayami Saori', '7c287fc8-8a14-49fc-8eca-84598834eb1d', 'śó©Ť¶čś≤ôÁĻĒ;śó©ŤßĀś≤ôÁĽá', 'Tokyo[8dc97297-ac95-4d33-82bc-e07fab26fb5f]', '100073[2db42837-c832-3c27-b4a3-08198f75693c]', '1991-05-29', NULL, '152;151;150;149;148;153;146;145;144;143;142', '200012', '2000707', '1', '[AllMusic (6)‚Ė†https://www.allmusic.com/artist/mn0003281376];[Internet Archive (6)‚Ė†https://web.archive.org/web/20190108135943/http://www.imenterprise.jp:80/data.php?id=66];[Anime Planet (6)‚Ė†https://www.anime-planet.com/people/saori-hayami];[Discogs (6)‚Ė†https://www.discogs.com/artist/2421652];[Spotify (3)‚Ė†https://open.spotify.com/artist/32UDgij5Tm7EtyRRCC1JTN];[IMDb (6)‚Ė†https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2977461/];[Last.fm (3)‚Ė†https://www.last.fm/music/%E6%97%A9%E8%A6%8B%E6%B2%99%E7%B9%94];[Official Website (2)‚Ė†https://hayamisaoriofficial.com/];[Rate Your Music (6)‚Ė†https://rateyourmusic.com/artist/%E6%97%A9%E8%A6%8B%E6%B2%99%E7%B9%94];[Anime News Network (6)‚Ė†https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/encyclopedia/people.php?id=63462];[Apple Music (3)‚Ė†https://music.apple.com/jp/artist/985532942];[Twitter (2)‚Ė†https://twitter.com/hayami_official];[VGMdb (6)‚Ė†https://vgmdb.net/artist/6876];[Wikidata (6)‚Ė†https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q1153079];[YouTube (3)‚Ė†https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCtUcK6HrhD024CkPDsURBwg];[Rutracker (5)‚Ė†https://rutracker.org/forum/tracker.php?nm=Hayami%20Saori];[The Pirate Bay (5)‚Ė†https://thepiratebay.org/search.php?q=Hayami+Saori&audio=on];[Wikipedia (6)‚Ė†https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hayami_Saori];[MusicBrainz (6)‚Ė†https://musicbrainz.org/artist/7c287fc8-8a14-49fc-8eca-84598834eb1d];[Genius (7)‚Ė†https://genius.com/artists/Hayami-Saori];[Instagram (2)‚Ė†https://www.instagram.com/hayamisaori_official]', 'Saori Hayami (śó©Ť¶č ś≤ôÁĻĒ, Hayami Saori, born May 29, 1991) is a Japanese voice actress and singer. Affiliated with the talent agency I\'m Enterprise, she has become one of the most prolific and recognizable voices in the anime industry, known for her soft, refined, and often mature vocal tone.\nHayami began her career in 2007 and has since voiced a wide array of prominent characters across television animation, films, and video games. She is particularly noted for her portrayals of Yukino Yukinoshita in My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU, Shinobu KochŇć in Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba, Yor Forger in Spy √ó Family, and ShŇćko Nishimiya in the critically acclaimed film A Silent Voice. Her performances have earned her several accolades, including the Best Supporting Actress award at the 10th Seiyu Awards in 2016.\nIn addition to voice acting, Hayami is a successful solo musical artist signed to Warner Bros. Home Entertainment Japan. She made her musical debut in 2015 with the single \"Yasashii Kibou,\" which served as the opening theme for Snow White with the Red Hair, an anime in which she also voiced the protagonist, Shirayuki. She is known for her involvement in the songwriting process, often writing lyrics and composing music for her own tracks and character songs.', 'http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/H/Hayami Saori/Audio/Albums/2018.12.19. JUNCTION/11. Jewelry.mp3^http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/H/Hayami Saori/Audio/Albums/2018.12.19. JUNCTION/04. Yume no Hate Made.mp3^http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/H/Hayami Saori/Audio/Singles/2018.03.28. Jewelry/02. Kohakutou.mp3', 'fallen down‚Ė†Shiroi Kokoro‚Ė†NAKED GENIUS‚Ė†Memory Heart Message‚Ė†Koi Kaze‚Ė†Shiroi Kokoro (TV Size)‚Ė†Ai no Yokan from Haqua‚Ė†Yasashii Kibou‚Ė†moon passport‚Ė†Kono Sekai ga Itsuka wa‚Ė†Namida iro‚Ė†Kaze ga Nanika wo Iou to Shiteru‚Ė†Komorebi no Contact‚Ė†Ryuusei‚Ė†Gokigen Ikaga?‚Ė†Filter‚Ė†Akai Hana Shiroi Hana‚Ė†Orange Mint‚Ė†nO limiT Violette starring Hayami Saori‚Ė†Michael ka Burial‚Ė†Omou Koto‚Ė†Memory Heart Message -Instrumental-‚Ė†Sono Koe ga Chizu ni Naru‚Ė†fallen down (TV Version)‚Ė†Shiroi Kokoro (Instrumental)‚Ė†Hello Alone -Yui Ballade-‚Ė†1%36st EVOLUTION‚Üí‚Ė†Miracle Way ~Tsuyoku Yasashiku Mamorarete~‚Ė†Danshou‚Ė†Shiroi Kokoro (Horaism)‚Ė†Blue H