†https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maaya_Sakamoto)];[MusicBrainz (6)‚Ė†https://musicbrainz.org/artist/b6c18308-82c7-4ec1-a42d-e8488bce6618];[Instagram (2)‚Ė†https://www.instagram.com/maayasakamoto_official];[TikTok (2)‚Ė†https://www.tiktok.com/@maayasakamoto_official]', 'Maaya Sakamoto (ŚĚāśú¨ ÁúüÁ∂ĺ, Sakamoto Maaya, born March 31, 1980) is a prolific Japanese singer-songwriter, actress, and voice actress. Since her professional debut at age eight, she has established herself as one of the most versatile and celebrated figures in the Japanese entertainment industry. Sakamoto is widely recognized for her extensive work in anime, video games, and musical theater, as well as her long-standing music career, which includes a decades-long collaboration with renowned composer Yoko Kanno. Sakamoto gained international fame for her role as Hitomi Kanzaki in The Vision of Escaflowne (1996). Other iconic roles include Ciel Phantomhive in Black Butler, Haruhi Fujioka in Ouran High School Host Club, Shinobu Oshino in the Monogatari series, and Motoko Kusanagi in Ghost in the Shell: Arise.\nShe is the voice of several prominent video game characters, including Aigis in Persona 3, Lightning in the Final Fantasy XIII trilogy, and Aerith Gainsborough in various Final Fantasy VII titles. She made her musical debut in 1996 with the single \"Yakusoku wa Iranai\". Over her 30-year music career, she has released 11 studio albums and 35 singles. Her 2011 album, You Can\'t Catch Me, became her first to reach number one on the Oricon charts. Beyond animation, Sakamoto is a respected stage actress, notably playing √Čponine in the Japanese production of Les Mis√©rables. She is also the official Japanese dub voice for Hollywood actresses such as Natalie Portman.', 'http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/M/Maaya Sakamoto/Audio/Compilations/1999.12.16. Single Collection+Hotchpotch/04. Gift.mp3^http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/M/Maaya Sakamoto/Audio/Compilations/1999.12.16. Single Collection+Hotchpotch/07. Light o