pop and anime music (anison) industries. She is widely recognized for performing the first opening theme of the anime Cardcaptor Sakura and for her work as a member of the musical duo Melocure. Hinata began her musical journey at the age of four by learning the piano. During the latter half of her elementary school years, she lived in the United States, where she developed a strong interest in songwriting. This period contributed to her fluency in English, a skill she frequently utilizes in her professional work by writing English lyrics and providing translation services for other artists.\n\nBeyond her vocal performances, Hinata is a prolific songwriter and lyricist. She is particularly noted for her work on the Monogatari series, writing lyrics for iconic tracks like \"Ren\'ai Circulation\" and \"Staple Stable.\" She has also composed and written for various popular artists, including Shoko Nakagawa (notably \"Sora-iro Days\"), Kana Hanazawa, and Nami Tamaki.', 'http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/M/Megumi Hinata/Audio/Singles/1999.04.22. Catch You Catch Me/01. Catch You Catch Me.mp3^http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/M/Megumi Hinata/Audio/Singles/1999.04.22. Catch You Catch Me/02. Hitorijime.mp3', 'Catch You Catch Me‚Ė†hirorijime (original karaoke)‚Ė†Chiisa na Uta‚Ė†ŚóöŚĎľ„ÄĀÁī†śôī„āČ„Āó„Āć„Éč„É£„É≥ÁĒü (feat. GUMI)‚Ė†Catch you, catch me‚Ė†Hitorijime‚Ė†Super Duper Love Love Days‚Ė†„Éí„Éą„É™„āł„É°‚Ė†ŚóöŚĎľ„ÄĀÁī†śôī„āČ„Āó„Āć„Éč„É£„É≥ÁĒü‚Ė†Chiisana Uta‚Ė†clover‚Ė†ŚóöŚĎľ„ÄĀÁī†śôī„āČ„Āó„Āć„Éč„É£„É≥ÁĒü (con GUMI)‚Ė†ŚóöŚĎľ„ÄĀÁī†śôī„āČ„Āó„Āć„Éč„É£„É≥ÁĒü (con Vocaloid Gumi)‚Ė†ŚóöŚĎľ„ÄĀÁī†śôī„āČ„Āó„Āć„Éč„É£„É≥ÁĒü (feat. Vocaloid Gumi)‚Ė†Catch You Catch Me (TV Size)‚Ė†Picnic‚Ė†Natsu no Mukougawa‚Ė†incl.‚Ė†1st Priority [Stratos 4]‚Ė†Catch You Catch Me(„ā™„É™„āł„Éä„Éę„ÉĽ„āę„É©„ā™„āĪ)‚Ė†hitorijime (feat. gumi)‚Ė†Catch me Catch you‚Ė†ŚóöŚĎľ„ÄĀÁī†śôī„āČ„Āó„Āć„Éč„É£„É≥ÁĒü (part. GUMI)‚Ė†Catch You, Catch Me! (Card Captor Sakura) (rŇćmaji karaoke)‚Ė†Baby Low Tension‚Ė†Ś§Ź„ĀģŚźĎ„Āď„ĀÜŚĀī‚Ė†Catch