(152, 'Megumi Kojima', '0d7cc47c-54fd-4ca2-9e8a-3fcb65ac2b89', 'Megumi Kojima', 'Yokohama[805ccce6-4760-4076-a2b2-dfbbd5d237cc]', '100073[2db42837-c832-3c27-b4a3-08198f75693c]', '1980-10-24', NULL, '153;151;150;149;148;147;146;145;144;143;142', '200006;200012', '2000031;2000707', '1', '[Discogs (6)‚Ė†https://www.discogs.com/artist/8024103];[Last.fm (6)‚Ė†https://www.last.fm/music/Megumi+Kojima];[MusicBrainz (6)‚Ė†https://musicbrainz.org/artist/0d7cc47c-54fd-4ca2-9e8a-3fcb65ac2b89];[IMDb (6)‚Ė†https://www.imdb.com/es/name/nm1327324/];[Apple Music (4)‚Ė†https://music.apple.com/us/artist/megumi-kojima/1323019012];[Spotify (3)‚Ė†https://open.spotify.com/artist/3ImLiVGMhQLxHNkvvzJqMG];[X (2)‚Ė†https://x.com/kojima_me];[VGMDb (6)‚Ė†https://vgmdb.net/artist/10261];[RuTracker (5)‚Ė†https://rutracker.org/forum/tracker.php?nm=Megumi%20Kojima];[The Pirate Bay (5)‚Ė†https://thepiratebay.org/search.php?q=Megumi+Kojima&audio=on]', 'Megumi Kojima (Japanese: ŚįŹŚ≥∂ „āĀ„Āź„ĀŅ, born October 24, 1980) is a Japanese voice actress and singer from Yokohama, Kanagawa Prefecture. She is best known for her roles in various anime series, most notably providing the voice for Fine in the Fushigiboshi no Futagohime series and performing theme music for popular franchises like Cardcaptor Sakura. Kojima began her career in the early 2000s, balancing roles as both a voice performer (seiyŇę) and a recording artist. Her breakout musical contribution came with the song \"Fruits Candy,\" which served as the third ending theme for the iconic anime series Cardcaptor Sakura. As a voice actress, she gained significant recognition for her leading role as Fine, one of the two main protagonists in Fushigiboshi no Futagohime (Twin Princesses of the Wonder Planet). Over the years, she has contributed to several high-profile projects. In addition to her character songs, Kojima is recognized for her soft, melodic vocals. Much of her discography is tied to the J-pop and anime genres, often appearing on compilatio