(153, 'Minori Suzuki', '722b9ee2-0415-452f-b655-dcd26f4ba5a4', '„Āô„Āö„Āć „ĀŅ„Āģ„āä', 'Aichi[4b190b90-aafd-4d87-8a51-95a710516176]', '100073[2db42837-c832-3c27-b4a3-08198f75693c]', '1997-10-01', NULL, '152;151;150;149;148;147;146;145;144;143;142', '200006;200012', '2000031;2000707', '1', '[Allmusic (6)‚Ė†https://www.allmusic.com/artist/mn0003697961];[discogs‚Ė†https://www.discogs.com/artist/5054899];[Spotify (3)‚Ė†https://open.spotify.com/artist/3Ath9xfI4WBdrZPFQ4VX9A];[Deezer (3)‚Ė†https://www.deezer.com/artist/14743203];[IMDb (6)‚Ė†https://www.imdb.com/name/nm8235009/];[Official Website (2)‚Ė†http://e-stone.victormusicarts.jp/minoringo/];[Rate Your Music (6)‚Ė†https://rateyourmusic.com/artist/%E9%88%B4%E6%9C%A8%E3%81%BF%E3%81%AE%E3%82%8A];[Anime News Network (6)‚Ė†https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/encyclopedia/people.php?id=143994];[Apple Music (4)‚Ė†https://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/id1036186784];[X (2)‚Ė†https://twitter.com/minoringo_staff];[Instagram (2)‚Ė†https://www.instagram.com/minoringo_official/];[VGMDb (6)‚Ė†https://vgmdb.net/artist/17552];[Wikidata (6)‚Ė†https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q22129371];[RuTracker (5)‚Ė†https://rutracker.org/forum/tracker.php?nm=Minori%20Suzuki];[The Pirate Bay (5)‚Ė†https://thepiratebay.org/search.php?q=Minori+Suzuki&audio=on]', 'Minori Suzuki (Japanese: ťąīśú® „ĀŅ„Āģ„āä, Hepburn: Suzuki Minori, born October 1, 1997) is a Japanese voice actress and singer from Aichi Prefecture. Affiliated with e-stone music, she rose to fame after winning the Macross Model Artist audition in 2015. Within the Cardcaptor Sakura franchise, she is best known for performing the second ending theme of the Clear Card arc, \"Rewind\" (2018), and for providing the voice of the character Akiho Shinomoto. Suzuki\'s career began with a massive breakout role as Freyja Wion in Macross Delta (2016), where she was a member of the idol group Walk√ľre. Her success in the Macross franchise established her as a powerful vocalist with a wide emotional range.\n\nIn 2018, she joined the cast of Cardcaptor Sakura: Clear Card as the mysterious transfer student Akiho Shinomoto. This role was significant as it required her to balance a cheerful, polite exterior with a sense of hidden melancholy. During the same period, she launched her solo music career under the FlyingDog label, with \"Rewind\" serving as one of her definitive early tracks. Suzuki is noted for her high-energy performance style and \"crystal-clear\" vocal tone. Her solo work often blends upbeat J-pop with elements of jazz and funk. In her Cardcaptor Sakura contributions, she adopted a softer, more nostalgic pop sound to match the \"magical girl\" aesthetic of the series.', 'http://127.0.0.1:8887//Music/M/Minori Suzuki/Audio/Albums/2018.12.19. Miru Mae ni Tobe!/08. FEELING AROUND.mp3', 'Wherever‚Ė†„É™„ÉĮ„ā§„É≥„ÉČ‚Ė†BROKEN IDENTITY‚Ė†Ś§úÁ©ļ‚Ė†FEELING AROUND‚Ė†„ÉÄ„É°„ÉŹ„ÉÄ„É°‚Ė†Saihate‚Ė†Musical‚Ė†Musical(TV EDIT)‚Ė†Saihate(TV EDIT)‚Ė†Wherever remix‚Ė†„ā®„Éē„āß„É°„É©„āí„Āā„Ā§„āĀ„Ā¶‚Ė†„Āĺ„Āľ„āć„Āó‚Ė†Crosswalk‚Ė†„É™„ÉĮ„ā§„É≥„ÉČ -TV„āĶ„ā§„āļ-‚Ė†Rut flower‚Ė†Lip‚Ė†My Own Story‚Ė†One More Melody‚Ė†śúÄśěú„Ā¶„Āģ„ÉŹ„É≠„Éľ‚Ė†But My Life More My Choice‚Ė†kisetsu no quartetto‚Ė†„āŹ„Āč„āČ„Ā™„ĀĄ„Āģ„āąBABY‚Ė†Ś•Ĺ„Āć„Ā™„āā„Āģ„ĀĮŚ•Ĺ„ĀćÔľĀ‚Ė†Now Is the Time!‚Ė†Linaria‚Ė†Summer Spring‚Ė†Shout!!!‚Ė†Hajimeyou‚Ė†„āŹ„Āü„Āó„ĀĮ„āŹ„Āü„Āó„Āę„Ā™„āä„Āü„ĀĄ‚Ė†Yozora‚Ė†„Āä„āĽ„É≥„ÉĀ„Ā™„É°„É≥„āŅ„Éę‚Ė†śúąŚ§ú„ĀģŚ§Ę‚Ė†Gloria‚Ė†„ĀĄ„Ā£„Āõ„Éľ„Āģ„Éľ„Āß„Ā£!‚Ė†Ť¶č„āčŚČć„Āęť£õ„ĀĻ!‚Ė†Tokimeki no Jikuu to Ringo‚Ė†„Āď„ĀĄ„āā„āą„ĀÜ‚Ė†„Āĺ„ĀĄ„Ā£„Ā°„āÉ„ĀÜ‚Ė†Ś•Ĺ„Āć„Ā™„āā„Āģ„ĀĮŚ•Ĺ„Āć!‚Ė†Ś§ßŚ•Ĺ„Āć„Āę„Ā™„Ā£„Ā¶„āą„Āč„Ā£„Āü‚Ė†ŤĆúÁ©ļ„ÄĀÁßĀ„ĀĆ„ĀĄ„ĀüŤ°ó‚Ė†„ÉÄ„É°„ÉŹ„ÉÄ„É°(šłä„Éü„Éé Ver.)‚Ė†astro traveler‚Ė†One More Step‚Ė†Śćäťü≥ťöé„Āģ„É¨„āł„āĻ„āŅ„É≥„āĻ‚Ė†ŚŅÉ„ĀĆ„ÄĀťĚí„ĀĄ„Äā‚Ė†20śČć„ĀģÁīĄśĚü‚Ė†„ĀĄ„Ā°„Āį„āďśúÄŚĺĆ„ĀģŚ§Ź‚Ė†„Éė„É≥„Ā™„Āď„Ā®„ĀĆ„Āó„Āü„ĀĄ!‚Ė†„āĶ„ā§„ÉŹ„ÉÜ‚Ė†Dame wa dame‚Ė†Ephemera wo Atsumete‚Ė†„Ā°„ĀĄ„Āē„Ā™„ĀŅ„Āģ„āä‚Ė†„Éü„É•„Éľ„āł„āę„Éę‚Ė†Rewind‚Ė†„É™„ÉÉ„Éó‚Ė†„āŹ„Ā†„Ā°„ĀģŤäĪ‚Ė†Ś≠£ÁĮÄ„Āģ„āę„Éę„ÉÜ„ÉÉ„Éą‚Ė†„Ā†„Ā£„Ā¶My Life „ā