(115, 'The Funeral of Hearts', NULL, '4', '2003.03.21.', 'BMG', 'Alternative Rock;Gothic Metal;Gothic Rock;Pop Rock', 'The Funeral of Hearts is a song by the Finnish band HIM, released in 2003. It is the second track and first single from the album Love Metal. It is one of HIMs most popular songs and was usually used to close live shows. It was nominated for the Kerrang! Award for Best Single.\nA music video was filmed for the song, produced by Stefan Lindfors. It was filmed in the surroundings of Ume√•, Sweden. It shows the band performing in a dream-like winter atmosphere in Lapland, and encountering mythical creatures. In 2004 it won a Kerrang! award for Best Video.', 'Bass‚†Ä‚ÄĘ‚†ÄDouble Bass~Lead Vocals‚†Ä‚ÄĘ‚†ÄGuitar~Guitar~Drums~Keyboard‚†Ä‚ÄĘ‚†ÄPiano', NULL, '476', '21‚Ė†22‚Ė†23‚Ė†27‚Ė†28', 'c2c74dce-0f7b-433b-9b90-948c86be4f7a', '~The Funeral of Hearts~[{22}]‚Ė†~Soul on Fire~[{22}]‚Ė†~Join Me In Death~[{22}]‚Ė†~Lonely Road~[{Daniel Lioneye_not_found}]‚Ė†~Hand of Doom~[{Black Sabbath_not_found}]', NULL, '~Lonely Road~[{63}]‚Ė†~Hand of Doom~[{Black Sabbath_not_found}]'),
(116, 'Buried Alive By Love', NULL, '4', '2003.10.06.', 'BMG', 'Alternative Rock;Gothic Metal;Gothic Rock;Pop Rock', 'Buried Alive by Love is a song by the Finnish rock band HIM, released in 2003. It is the first track and second single from the album Love Metal. The music video was directed by Bam Margera. Margera has also directed three other music videos for the band, those being The Sacrament, Solitary Man and And Love Said No. The music video features actress Juliette Lewis.', 'Bass‚†Ä‚ÄĘ‚†ÄDouble Bass~Lead Vocals‚†Ä‚ÄĘ‚†ÄGuitar~Guitar~Drums~Keyboard‚†Ä‚ÄĘ‚†ÄPiano', NULL, '4_bnd', '21‚Ė†22‚Ė†23‚Ė†27‚Ė†28', 'fe048cc6-34b6-41b1-a1c3-8ce7109fe340', '~Buried Alive By Love~[{22}]‚Ė†~Hand of Doom~[{Black Sabbath_not_found}]‚Ė†~Buried Alive by Love~[{22}]‚Ė†~Lonely Road~[{Daniel Lioneye_not_found}]', NULL, '~Hand of Doom~[{Black Sabbath_not_found}]'),
(121, 'HIM World Tribute', NULL, '120', '2020.02.26.', 'Self-released record', NULL, 'HIM World Tribute is a heartfelt homage to the iconic Finnish band HIM, reimagining their most beloved tracks through a fresh yet faithful lens. Released in 2020, this 13-song compilation spans nearly an hour of reinterpretations, including fan favorites like ‚ÄúJoin Me,‚ÄĚ ‚ÄúSleepwalking Past Hope,‚ÄĚ and ‚ÄúKilling Loneliness.‚ÄĚ It captures the emotional intensity and gothic romanticism that defined HIM‚Äôs sound, while adding subtle production touches that honor the originals without overshadowing them. It‚Äôs a sonic love letter for fans who want to relive the magic‚ÄĒand for newcomers ready to discover the beauty of love metal through a tribute that resonates deeply.', NULL, NULL, '467', NULL, '', '~For You~[{23};{22}]‚Ė†~Sleepwalking Past Hope~[{22}]‚Ė†~Resurrection~[{Him_not_found};{22}]‚Ė†~And Love Said No~[{22}]‚Ė†~Join Me in Death~[{22}]‚Ė†~Poison Girl~[{22}]‚Ė†~The Sacrament~[{22}]‚Ė†~The Kiss of Dawn~[{22}]‚Ė†‚Ė†~Pretending~[{22}]‚Ė†~This Fortress of Tears~[{447};{22}]‚Ė†~Bury Me Deep Inside Your Heart~[{22}]‚Ė†~Right Here in My Arms~[{22}]', '~Sleepwalking Past Hope~[{Julia Tallina_not_found}]‚Ė†~Resurrection~;[Andrew Zubekhin_not_found}]‚Ė†~And Love Said No~[Kirill Pysarenko_not_found}]‚Ė†~Join Me in Death~[[Alexey Shmanev_not_found}]‚Ė†~Poison Girl~[Natalie Gioia_not_found}]‚Ė†~The Sacrament~[Fabio Phobos_not_found}]‚Ė†~The Kiss of Dawn~[Julia Tallina_not_found}]‚Ė†~Killing Loneliness~[Andrew Zubekhin_not_found}]‚Ė†~Pretending~[Lena Shed_not_found}]‚Ė†~This Fortress of Tears~[Max Ivashenko_not_found}]‚Ė†~Bury Me Deep Inside Your Heart~[Darina Lozinskaya_not_found}]‚Ė†~Right Here in My Arms~[Vasiliy Hotsko_not_found}]', '~For You~[{4_bnd}]‚Ė†~Sleepwalking Past Hope~[{4_bnd}]‚Ė†~Resurrection~[{4_bnd}]‚Ė†~And Love Said No~[{4_bnd}]‚Ė†~Join Me in Death~[{4_bnd}]‚Ė†~Poison Girl~[{4_bnd}]‚Ė†~The Sacrament~[{4_bnd}]‚Ė†~The Kiss of Dawn~[{4_bnd}]‚Ė†~Killing Loneliness~[{4_