(216, 'Tuomarin Todistajat', NULL, '120', '2000.01.12.', 'Megamania', 'Alternative Rock;Pop Rock', 'Tuomarin Todistajat is a Finnish rock compilation released in 2000, featuring 13 tracks by a diverse lineup of artists including Ville Valo, YUP, Egotrippi, J. Karjalainen Electric Sauna, and Sielun Veljet. The album showcases a rich tapestry of styles‚ÄĒfrom atmospheric ballads to gritty rock anthems‚ÄĒeach contributing a unique interpretation of themes tied to Finnish musical identity and storytelling. With contributions from both mainstream and alternative acts, the compilation serves as a tribute to the influential legacy of Finnish rock, offering listeners a curated journey through the genre\'s emotional and sonic range.', NULL, NULL, '120_bnd', NULL, '0c015ca0-cf9e-4d92-bf2a-2e48c48d4a26', '~Valo Y√∂ss√§~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Lasten Mehuhetki~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Suuri Peto~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Viini√§! Malja Marttyyreille~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Hotelli Voodoo~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Punainen Planeetta~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Kaalimaan Kansa~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Sunnuntaina~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~On Aika Soittaa Sinfonia~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Rion Satamassa~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Ramona~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Laaksossa~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Huda Huda!~[{Various Artists_not_found}]', '~Huda Huda!~{Nylon Beat_not_found}]', NULL),
(220, 'Synkkien laulujen maa', NULL, '120', '2006.11.22.', 'Universal', 'Alternative Rock;Pop Rock', 'Synkkien laulujen maa is a Finnish compilation album released in 2006, featuring new interpretations of melancholic and emotionally resonant songs by a wide range of Finnish artists. Inspired by a Helsingin Sanomat article series and a public vote conducted with Radio Helsinki, the album brings together iconic tracks that reflect the darker side of Finnish musical storytelling. With performances by artists like Ville Valo, Kari Tapio, Katri Ylander, Tuomari Nurmio, and Paula Vesala, the compilation blends pop, rock, and folk influences into a cohesive tribute to sorrowful yet beautiful songwriting. It reached #4 on Finland‚Äôs official charts and earned gold certification in 2008, underscoring its cultural impact and emotional depth.', NULL, NULL, '120_bnd', NULL, 'a25e4995-b30a-41a8-9372-271874337b15', '~Peltoniemen Hintriikan surumarssi~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Lumi teki enkelin eteiseen~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Joutsenlaulu~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Yksin√§inen~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Oi mutsi mutsi~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~T√§√§ll√§ Pohjant√§hden alla~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Murheellisten laulujen maa~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Pime√§ tie‚Ė† mukavaa matkaa~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Tyhj√§√§~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~El√§m√§n valttikortit~[{Various Artists_not_found}]‚Ė†~Maria Magdalena~[{Ari H√§m√§l√§inen_not_found};{Jouni M√∂mm√∂_not_found}]‚Ė†~Kun min√§ kotoani l√§ksin~[{Various Artists_not_found}]', '~T√§√§ll√§ Pohjant√§hden alla~{62_bnd}]‚Ė†~Pime√§ tie# mukavaa matkaa~{Olavi Uusivirta_not_found}]‚Ė†~Kun min√§ kotoani l√§ksin~{Tommi Viksten_not_found}]', '~Maria Magdalena~[{Mana Mana_not_found}]'),
